      "date": "2016-10-26 09:16:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI wouldn't be against removing s2dhms() either, since it isnt the kernel's job to convert the time format.  It was originally added over my objections as a way to be more \"user friendly\", but it isn't clear this is more important than any other timestamp we print:\n\n client# lctl get_param mdc.*.timeouts\n mdc.myth-MDT0000-mdc-ffff880075147800.timeouts=\n last reply : 1477473133, 0d0h00m06s ago\n network    : cur   1  worst   2 (at 1476410241, 12d7h14m58s ago)   1   1   1   1 \n portal 12  : cur   1  worst  31 (at 1476873635, 6d22h31m44s ago)   1   1   1   1 \n portal 30  : cur   1  worst   1 (at 1476332894, 13d4h44m05s ago)   1   0   0   0 \n portal 23  : cur   1  worst  31 (at 1476410241, 12d7h14m58s ago)   1   0   0   0 \n portal 17  : cur   1  worst  31 (at 1476873598, 6d22h32m21s ago)   1   0   0   0 \n\nAlso, it is easy to convert the seconds value into a real time if needed:\n\n client# date --date=@1476410241\n Thu Oct 13 19:57:21 MDT 2016",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
